data.label:
LineNo: 4091658,

Narrator: Lileas sighed.
en


Lileas sighed.

LineNo: 4091760,

Narrator: Nia Morgna and Lileas Graf schedule...
en


Nia Morgna and Lileas Graf scheduled a meeting to discuss an ongoing legal case that required my attention.

LineNo: 4091868,

Narrator: Early in the morning, we convened i...
en


Early in the morning, we convened in my office.

LineNo: 4091976,

Lileas Graf: Thank you for being here at this h...
en


"Thank you for being here at this hour, Mr. President."

LineNo: 4092078,

Nia Morgna: There is a court case initiated by...
en


"There is a court case initiated by a Bludish citizen which involves a possible revision of the constitution. Unfortunately, it has the potential to affect the whole country."

LineNo: 4092196,

Narrator: Nia stacked the papers in front of...
en


Nia stacked the papers in front of her.

LineNo: 4092576,

Lileas Graf: We need to inform you about some n...
en


"We need to inform you about some news from Bergia."

LineNo: 4092678,

Player: I'm listening.
en


"I'm listening."

LineNo: 4092780,

Player: Explain, please.
en


"Explain, please."

LineNo: 4092882,

Player: Great. Bad news from Bergia again....
en


"Great. Bad news from Bergia again. What's new?"

LineNo: 4092984,

Lileas Graf: I'll start from the beginning. As...
en


"I'll start from the beginning. As you know, after the discovery of KA-74s in separatist hideouts, there have been more than a few attacks initiated and claimed by the BFF."

LineNo: 4093086,

Lileas Graf: However, with the rising tensions...
en


"However, with the rising tensions after Operation Bear Trap, we have also been receiving more and more intelligence about some kind of a 'preparation' by the terrorists."

LineNo: 4093188,

Lileas Graf: Due to the decrease of security fu...
en


"Due to the decrease of security funds, many of these -- otherwise avoidable -- attacks couldn't be stopped. This created some hysteria inside Bergia."

LineNo: 4093568,

Lileas Graf: Thanks to the increase in security...
en


"Thanks to the increase in security funding, many of these attacks were stopped before they were executed."

LineNo: 4093670,

Lileas Graf: Due to the lack of security fundin...
en


"Due to the lack of security funding, some of these -- otherwise avoidable -- attacks couldn't be stopped. This led to some increase in the tensions in Bergia."

LineNo: 4094050,

Nia Morgna: Unfortunately, the court backlog i...
en


"Unfortunately, the court backlog is piling up with increasingly frequent rulings that are unjust. This has led to many of our citizens losing their trust in our justice system. This is particularly a problem for the residents of Bergia."

LineNo: 4094152,

Lileas Graf: It increased even further after Op...
en


"It increased even further after Operation Bear Trap. We have been receiving more and more intelligence about some kind of a 'preparation' by the terrorists."

LineNo: 4094254,

Nia Morgna: It's definitely not helping with t...
en


"It's definitely not helping with the increasing tensions between the Bludish populace and Sords."

LineNo: 4094356,

Player: This is worrying.
en


"This is worrying."

LineNo: 4094458,

Player: I think the threat is overblown.
en


"I think the threat is overblown."

LineNo: 4094560,

Player: You have my ear.
en


"You have my ear."

LineNo: 4094662,

Lileas Graf: We'll get there, Ms. Morgna. As I...
en


"We'll get there, Ms. Morgna. As I was saying..."

LineNo: 4094764,

Nia Morgna: I agree with you that the threat h...
en


"I agree with you that the threat has been exaggerated. However, the court case that I'm looking ov-"

LineNo: 4094866,

Lileas Graf: The increasing threat of the BFF l...
en


"The increasing threat of the BFF led Governor Bron to -- justifiably -- resort to his emergency powers to curb the danger."

LineNo: 4094968,

Lileas Graf: His discovery of militant training...
en


"His discovery of militant training grounds disguised as schools was commendable, as well as his quick handling of bomb threats coming from major cities like Deyr."

LineNo: 4095070,

Lileas Graf: However, his latest policies have...
en


"However, his latest policies have been questionable. Especially the 'Peaceful Resettlement' order. It has been met with massive anger from the majority of the Bluds in the region."

LineNo: 4095172,

Player: What exactly is this case about?
en


"What exactly is this case about?"

LineNo: 4095274,

Nia Morgna: Ishval Ersen is claiming that the...
en


"Ishval Ersen is claiming that the current constitution gives the legal grounds to discriminate against Bludish people, directly infringing upon their rights as citizens."

LineNo: 4095376,

Nia Morgna: He claims Article 7 of the constit...
en


"He claims Article 7 of the constitution -- citing the line: 'Every Sord is equal before the law' -- is in direct conflict with the freedoms and rights defined in Article 100."

LineNo: 4095478,

Nia Morgna: Governor Phelix Bron is accused of...
en


"Governor Phelix Bron is accused of using Article 7 to justify his oppression of the Bludish community."

LineNo: 4095580,

Player: What are the accusations against t...
en


"What are the accusations against the governor?"

LineNo: 4095682,

Player: Who is Ishval Ersen?
en


"Who is Ishval Ersen?"

LineNo: 4095784,

Lileas Graf: Mr. Bron has sadly evicted thousan...
en


"Mr. Bron has sadly evicted thousands of Bluds from their homes in Deyr recently. The fact that this happened in a city with relatively low levels of BFF activity is a sloppy decision at best."

LineNo: 4095886,

Nia Morgna: A sloppy decision? This is a direc...
en


"A sloppy decision? This is a direct violation of their right to property. The BFF activity levels have nothing to do with this."

LineNo: 4095988,

Lileas Graf: But it does, Ms. Morgna. The state...
en


"But it does, Ms. Morgna. The state can take any measures to fight with terror inside its borders. The decision would have been justified if those neighborhoods were in fact labelled as 'threat level red'."

LineNo: 4096090,

Lileas Graf: ...But they were not. Hence, he di...
en


"...But they were not. Hence, he did not have the authority to evict those citizens. In this case in Deyr, the governor has definitely violated his authority."

LineNo: 4096192,

Nia Morgna: There are hundreds of accusations...
en


"There are hundreds of accusations listed in this case, ranging from violent actions by law enforcement officers to open discrimination in local municipalities."

LineNo: 4096294,

Nia Morgna: You are underplaying it. This evic...
en


"You are underplaying it. This eviction was only the last of the many he ordered as part of Bergia's *peaceful resettlement policies*. This is not about Deyr."

LineNo: 4096396,

Nia Morgna: Ishval Ersen is a lawyer and Bludi...
en


"Ishval Ersen is a lawyer and Bludish rights activist. He lives in Deyr and has experienced the systemic racism in the region firsthand."

LineNo: 4096498,

Nia Morgna: He was evicted last month from his...
en


"He was evicted last month from his home in Deyr on the grounds of 'threatening public stability and safety'."

LineNo: 4096600,

Nia Morgna: He was also shot at by local law e...
en


"He was also shot at by local law enforcement forces several times in the last two years and managed to survive it all so far. The attackers, of course, were never punished."

LineNo: 4096702,

Lileas Graf: As much as the eviction seems unju...
en


"As much as the eviction seems unjust, Mr. Ersen must be further investigated for his potential ties to dangerous organizations. I'd like to believe the forces wouldn't have fired at him without proper reason."

LineNo: 4096820,

Player: What exactly does Ersen claim abou...
en


"What exactly does Ersen claim about the conflict in the constitution?"

LineNo: 4096922,

Nia Morgna: As you know, the rights and libert...
en


"As you know, the rights and liberties Article 7 alludes to are described in Article 100 in further detail."

LineNo: 4097024,

Nia Morgna: Mr. Ersen claims the line: 'Every...
en


"Mr. Ersen claims the line: 'Every Sord is equal before the law' in Article 7 does not include other ethnicities and thus gives the state the right to suspend or limit the rights of non-Sords defined in Article 100."

LineNo: 4097126,

Nia Morgna: All citizens, in theory, can exerc...
en


"All citizens, in theory, can exercise their rights described in these articles and are equally subject to law as described, and these rights cannot be suspended by the government under any circumstances other than a defensive war."

LineNo: 4097228,

Nia Morgna: Courts have repeatedly protected G...
en


"Courts have repeatedly protected Governor Bron in the past, and it is true that he bets on Mr. Hawker justifying his actions through Article 7. However, there is also Article 6 -- which the courts could have taken into account already."

LineNo: 4097354,

Player: And what is the problem with Artic...
en


"And what is the problem with Article 6?"

LineNo: 4097456,

Player: Article 7 is an embarrassment that...
en


"Article 7 is an embarrassment that needs to be removed. I wish we could also tackle this in our proposal for constitutional change."

LineNo: 4097558,

Player: Explain.
en


"Explain."

LineNo: 4097660,

Nia Morgna: I'm not sure how you'd manage that...
en


"I'm not sure how you'd manage that at this stage of the process."

LineNo: 4097762,

Nia Morgna: As you know, Article 6 goes: 'Ever...
en


"As you know, Article 6 goes: 'Everyone who is bound to the Sordish state by citizenship is a Sord'."

LineNo: 4097864,

Nia Morgna: But did you ask Bludish people wha...
en


"But did you ask Bludish people what they think? Yes, it's true that this article has protected them on a number of occasions, as it defines Sord as a non-ethnic term, but it is left up to the interpretation of the courts."

LineNo: 4097966,

Lileas Graf: Which clarifies clearly that the c...
en


"Which clarifies clearly that the constitution does not discriminate against other ethnicities or cultures. Citizens of this country are called Sords."

LineNo: 4098068,

Nia Morgna: They could have argued that Articl...
en


"They could have argued that Article 6 extends the rights defined in Article 7 to all citizens of Sordland regardless of race. But they didn't. Yet."

LineNo: 4098170,

Player: This is getting very complicated.
en


"This is getting very complicated."

LineNo: 4098272,

Nia Morgna: I'll try to keep it simple.
en


"I'll try to keep it simple."

LineNo: 4098374,

Nia Morgna: That is a massive understatement....
en


"That is a massive understatement. Governor Bron has abused his powers and clearly acted against the constitution."

LineNo: 4098476,

Nia Morgna: And quite surprisingly, Ishval Ers...
en


"And quite surprisingly, Ishval Ersen has managed to successfully push his case to the higher courts. He is suing Phelix Bron for infringing upon the liberties of Bludish people."

LineNo: 4098578,

Nia Morgna: He also raises a conflict in the c...
en


"He also raises a conflict in the constitution and argues that the way it is written makes it open to interpretation and allows people like Governor Bron to abuse their powers."

LineNo: 4098958,

Nia Morgna: It wasn't a possibility according...
en


"It wasn't a possibility according to the preliminary committee meetings."

LineNo: 4099060,

Nia Morgna: But there might be a way around it...
en


"But there might be a way around it in the near future."

LineNo: 4099162,

Nia Morgna: They can potentially push this cas...
en


"They can potentially push this case to the Supreme Court."

LineNo: 4100052,

Player: I have enough information.
en


"I have enough information."

LineNo: 4100522,

Nia Morgna: In any case... The situation might...
en


"In any case... The situation might be troubling if it reaches the Supreme Court and Mr. Hawker manages to sabotage it by altering the current interpretation. It would be disastrous for Bludish rights."

LineNo: 4100624,

Nia Morgna: I will be doing my best to ensure...
en


"I will be doing my best to ensure a positive result comes out of this case. But I'm not sure if the centrists would be willing to agree with Mr. Ersen."

LineNo: 4100726,

Lileas Graf: Why would Mr. Hawker even sabotage...
en


"Why would Mr. Hawker even sabotage it? The current interpretation is strictly Sollist. I'm sure he will follow the constitution and charge Governor Bron for unconstitutional behavior."

LineNo: 4100828,

Lileas Graf: According to the foundational valu...
en


"According to the foundational values of this republic, everyone who is a citizen of this country is a Sord. The constitution is clear about this and does not allow for discrimination."

LineNo: 4100930,

Nia Morgna: Maybe Hawker is not the man you th...
en


"Maybe Hawker is not the man you think he is, Ms. Graf. From what I've heard, his stance on this subject may not be the standard Sollist interpretation but... something darker."

LineNo: 4101032,

Nia Morgna: I'm afraid he'll reject the case a...
en


"I'm afraid he'll reject the case altogether and find Governor Bron innocent. If this happens, it would make discrimination against Bludish people legal."

LineNo: 4101150,

Player: Do you think Justice Hawker and th...
en


"Do you think Justice Hawker and the Old Guards would go that far?"

LineNo: 4101252,

Player: What if we can convince the Justic...
en


"What if we can convince the Justices to agree with Ersen? Wouldn't that give us precedent to change said articles of the constitution?"

LineNo: 4101354,

Player: This is insane. Isn't there anythi...
en


"This is insane. Isn't there anything I can do?"

LineNo: 4101456,

Nia Morgna: According to the rumors within the...
en


"According to the rumors within the Supreme Court, yes. It is already unusual that the case is making its way up to them."

LineNo: 4101558,

Nia Morgna: If the Supreme Court agrees that t...
en


"If the Supreme Court agrees that the constitution is in conflict with itself, yes... But I don't know if you are serious or not, Mr. President."

LineNo: 4101660,

Nia Morgna: I'm afraid not, Mr. President. The...
en


"I'm afraid not, Mr. President. The executive has no jurisdiction over the judiciary."

LineNo: 4101762,

Player: You must put pressure on the syste...
en


"You must put pressure on the system and block this case from reaching the Supreme Court, Ms. Morgna."

LineNo: 4101864,

Nia Morgna: I'm afraid even Justice Edmonds an...
en


"I'm afraid even Justice Edmonds and the centrists would be completely against that. It would be a very difficult scenario."

LineNo: 4101966,

Nia Morgna: And in this case, I'm afraid even...
en


"And in this case, I'm afraid even Justice Edmonds and the centrists would be almost impossible to convince."

LineNo: 4102068,

Nia Morgna: Of course. I will do my best, Mr....
en


"Of course. I will do my best, Mr. President."

LineNo: 4102170,

Lileas Graf: To be honest, I don't think this i...
en


"To be honest, I don't think this is a matter for our administration. We must keep out from judicial affairs."

LineNo: 4102272,

Player: Honestly, I couldn't care less. It...
en


"Honestly, I couldn't care less. It would be better for this country."

LineNo: 4102374,

Narrator: Nia recoiled with shock.
en


Nia recoiled with shock.

LineNo: 4102476,

Nia Morgna: I hope you are joking, Mr. Preside...
en


"I hope you are joking, Mr. President."

LineNo: 4102578,

Player: What the Bludish community is goin...
en


"What the Bludish community is going through in Bergia is unacceptable. We must do what it takes to stop this madness."

LineNo: 4102680,

Player: Ms. Graf is right. We must first b...
en


"Ms. Graf is right. We must first be completely sure that Mr. Ersen is innocent."

LineNo: 4102782,

Player: Are you joking, Ms. Graf? You'd li...
en


"Are you joking, Ms. Graf? You'd like to *believe*? The police are getting out of control under your management."

LineNo: 4102884,

Lileas Graf: What does that supposed to mean? I...
en


"What does that supposed to mean? I'm not even in control of the forces that are being blamed here. Governor Bron has his own security forces."

LineNo: 4102986,

Nia Morgna: That we must.
en


"That we must."

LineNo: 4103088,

Lileas Graf: I will look into it, Mr. President.
en


"I will look into it, Mr. President."

LineNo: 4103190,

Lileas Graf: My forces were not involved in any...
en


"My forces were not involved in any of this. It was Bergian police. Bergia's special zone is what allowed this to happen in the first place."

LineNo: 4103292,

Nia Morgna: As much as I hate to say it, I som...
en


"As much as I hate to say it, I somewhat agree with Lileas on this. I'd prefer to keep the status quo over risking a complete abolishment of rights. We still have the power to make tangible reforms."

LineNo: 4103418,

Player: Your lack of faith is disappointin...
en


"Your lack of faith is disappointing. I must say I didn't expect that from you. And what about your tangible reforms?"

LineNo: 4103520,

Nia Morgna: I'm simply stating the obvious, Mr...
en


"I'm simply stating the obvious, Mr. President. Instead of openly attacking the court, we can bring real change with our lawmaking powers."

LineNo: 4103622,

Lileas Graf: As I said, I think the government...
en


"As I said, I think the government has better things to do than meddle with judicial affairs."

LineNo: 4103724,

Lileas Graf: There is, however, something that...
en


"There is, however, something that the government can do to address the situation on the ground."

LineNo: 4103826,

Lileas Graf: It is time we push for change with...
en


"It is time we push for change within the security structure of Bergia and the special status that resulted in de facto autonomy. It clearly isn't working."

LineNo: 4103928,

Nia Morgna: The resettlement policies in Bergi...
en


"The resettlement policies in Bergia and the Ersen case have changed the mood of the lawmakers. We can use this opportunity to push for the removal of Tarquin Soll's security zone decree. It is a much bigger possibility than before."

LineNo: 4104030,

Lileas Graf: Ms. Morgna is right. There is some...
en


"Ms. Morgna is right. There is something that the government can do to address the situation on the ground."

LineNo: 4104132,

Nia Morgna: Of course racism is rampant throug...
en


"Of course racism is rampant throughout our country, but Bludish citizens inside Bergia are having a much worse time than the Bludish residents of cities like Lachaven or Holsord. If we focus on Bergia, we can remove its special status."

LineNo: 4104234,

Nia Morgna: This alone would be a huge step fo...
en


"This alone would be a huge step for Bludish rights. Unfortunately, as long as Governor Bron is in charge of Bergia with the powers he has, no judicial reforms would reverse the situation on the ground."

LineNo: 4104336,

Lileas Graf: To put it simply, we want to work...
en


"To put it simply, we want to work on a detailed proposal to restructure Bergia. I believe it must become a region of Sordland like any other. We must centralize the system and abolish the local security forces."

LineNo: 4104438,

Player: Are you absolutely certain that yo...
en


"Are you absolutely certain that your security forces can do a better job than Bergian police?"

LineNo: 4104540,

Player: I don't see how a local change is...
en


"I don't see how a local change is more important than removing the basis of discrimination in our very constitution."

LineNo: 4104642,

Player: Are you sure we can even revoke th...
en


"Are you sure we can even revoke the special status of Bergia?"

LineNo: 4105578,

Player: You are right. We shouldn't meddle...
en


"You are right. We shouldn't meddle in the judiciary."

LineNo: 4105680,

Player: I don't agree with changing the st...
en


"I don't agree with changing the structure in Bergia now. We shouldn't disrupt Governor Bron's policies."

LineNo: 4105782,

Nia Morgna: We can't be sure of anything, Mr....
en


"We can't be sure of anything, Mr. President. You know this better than me."

LineNo: 4105884,

Lileas Graf: It is true. Some members of my cir...
en


"It is true. Some members of my circle inside the party are keen on this as well. They are starting to believe Soll's policy in Bergia has already run its course."

LineNo: 4105986,

Nia Morgna: But Lileas and I both believe ther...
en


"But Lileas and I both believe there is potential to get more MPs behind the idea."

LineNo: 4106088,

Lileas Graf: It is discouraging to hear this fr...
en


"It is discouraging to hear this from you, Mr. President. My team and our officers on the ground are comprised of the most well-trained and patriotic individuals."

LineNo: 4106190,

Lileas Graf: With Bergia under complete control...
en


"With Bergia under complete control of the central administration, we will no longer hear about reports of injustice against our Bludish citizens."

LineNo: 4106292,

Lileas Graf: We can't allow the conflict in Weh...
en


"We can't allow the conflict in Wehlen to spread to Sordland. And we know that the Wehlen and Sordland divisions of the BFF are in close cooperation."

LineNo: 4106418,

Nia Morgna: Well, Mr. President, if your insan...
en


"Well, Mr. President, if your insane proposal somehow makes it, your new powers would allow you to enact this by decree anyway."

LineNo: 4106520,

Nia Morgna: If we play our cards right during...
en


"If we play our cards right during the process of this case while we work on the preparation of a strong proposal for the special zone, we can gather enough support behind it."

LineNo: 4106622,

Nia Morgna: Well, Mr. President, with a strong...
en


"Well, Mr. President, with a strong enough proposal and some judicial support, your current powers might be just enough to be able to enact this by decree as well."

LineNo: 4106724,

Nia Morgna: We have to try.
en


"We have to try."

LineNo: 4106842,

Nia Morgna: In any case, I think it is also po...
en


"In any case, I think it is also possible to get this through the Assembly."

LineNo: 4107034,

BergiaMeetingJumpPointA
Title en


BergiaMeetingJumpPointA

LineNo: 4107160,

Player: Okay. Let's hear about the proposa...
en


"Okay. Let's hear about the proposal."

LineNo: 4107262,

Player: Why stop with Bergia? We have to e...
en


"Why stop with Bergia? We have to eventually change Articles 6 and 7 as well."

LineNo: 4107364,

Lileas Graf: Nia and I both agree that we need...
en


"Nia and I both agree that we need to abolish the Special Zone of Bergia. This is the first point that the proposal will address."

LineNo: 4107466,

Player: I think this might be too risky to...
en


"I think this might be too risky to push at the same time with our constitutional amendments."

LineNo: 4107568,

Nia Morgna: I'm glad that we agree. Of course...
en


"I'm glad that we agree. Of course we should push for that in our next amendments."

LineNo: 4107670,

Nia Morgna: It's not. But when the forces on t...
en


"It's not. But when the forces on the ground don't even respect the constitution, fixing it alone would not suffice."

LineNo: 4107772,

Lileas Graf: Let's wake up to the real world. T...
en


"Let's wake up to the real world. There is no way the Assembly or the Court would pass an amendment to Article 6 or 7."

LineNo: 4107874,

Nia Morgna: If our current proposal passes, we...
en


"If our current proposal passes, we will no longer need the Court to change the constitution."

LineNo: 4108262,

Nia Morgna: And the Assembly can always be con...
en


"And the Assembly can always be convinced later."

LineNo: 4108462,

Player: I still think we can add these ame...
en


"I still think we can add these amendments to our proposal before the vote. The current proposal can still be modified."

LineNo: 4108564,

Lileas Graf: You can do whatever you want with...
en


"You can do whatever you want with your amendments, Mr. President. But at least hear about our proposal first."

LineNo: 4108666,

Nia Morgna: I'm not going to deny the risk but...
en


"I'm not going to deny the risk but we can no longer look away."

LineNo: 4108768,

Lileas Graf: Before we get distracted, I'd like...
en


"Before we get distracted, I'd like to briefly talk about the details of the proposal."

LineNo: 4108870,

Nia Morgna: I can't believe it. Are you really...
en


"I can't believe it. Are you really supportive of Governor Bron's policies, Mr. President?"

LineNo: 4108996,

Lileas Graf: On the other hand, the community p...
en


"On the other hand, the community police have been very helpful in the areas where they were allowed to serve -- which aren't many, unfortunately."

LineNo: 4109376,

Lileas Graf: The main problem is with the secur...
en


"The main problem is with the security structure of Bergia. Due to the special status of the region, operations on the ground are run by local security forces that are not bound to the Interior."

LineNo: 4109478,

Lileas Graf: Which means my hands are tied.
en


"Which means my hands are tied."

LineNo: 4109858,

Player: That's precisely why we joined the...
en


"That's precisely why we joined the operation. To destroy the BFF once and for all."

LineNo: 4110238,

Player: That's precisely why we're coopera...
en


"That's precisely why we're cooperating with Wehzek forces to defend our borders."

LineNo: 4110340,

Nia Morgna: The main problem is not security b...
en


"The main problem is not security but the very right to existence of the Bludish people. I'd still like to believe your perspective can be changed on this subject."

LineNo: 4110442,

Lileas Graf: This would also mean taking away t...
en


"This would also mean taking away the special authority of the governor."

LineNo: 4110544,

Nia Morgna: I agree with removing the governor...
en


"I agree with removing the governor as well as his insane authority. But I don't support a complete centralization of the region. I propose that we restructure the Special Zone, democratize it and acknowledge the Bludish movement."

LineNo: 4110646,

Lileas Graf: How does that resolve anything? Ho...
en


"How does that resolve anything? How do you solve any problem by dividing the region from the rest of Sordland? We've tried that already."

LineNo: 4110764,

Lileas Graf: My proposal is very simple. The sp...
en


"My proposal is very simple. The special zone must be fully revoked, governor's powers taken away and the local security forces must be abolished. Only then Bergia can be an equal part of Sordland."

LineNo: 4110866,

Lileas Graf: We will hold local municipal elect...
en


"We will hold local municipal elections just like every city in Sordland, and the security of the region will be under the full control of the Ministry of the Interior. We can no longer allow their forces to pursue violence with impunity."

LineNo: 4110968,

Nia Morgna: If this was a problem that the cen...
en


"If this was a problem that the central government could fix, your mighty Colonel would have solved it already. The assimilation policies clearly didn't work."

LineNo: 4111070,

Nia Morgna: Millions of Bludish people suffere...
en


"Millions of Bludish people suffered over the last decades. We saw a massive uprising, terror attacks and a governor going rogue. These people only wanted to live in this country as equals, but they were denied that."

LineNo: 4111172,

Nia Morgna: Why don't we allow Bergians to ele...
